comments: Trent Jr. (TOR) makes clean ball contact on his attempt to tap it away from Lowry (MIA) and marginal side to side follow-through contact occurs during the rebound.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Trent Jr.'s (TOR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

An inadvertent whistle is blown for what is believed to be a timeout called by the Toronto bench. After crew discussion, it was determined no timeout was requested and play resumes with Toronto maintaining possession.
Anunoby (TOR) firms up over his right leg in Vincent's (MIA) path and absorbs the contact to his upper body.  Any ensuing foot to foot contact that occurs as they separate is considered incidental.
Siakam (TOR) brings his hands toward Vincent (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as Siakam releases away to roll.
Vincent (MIA) legally contests Siakam's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Achiuwa (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges the ball from Herro (MIA) as they pursue the rebound.
Achiuwa (TOR) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Miami.
Adebayo (MIA) firms up in VanVleet's (TOR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Trent Jr. (TOR) makes clean ball contact to temporarily dislodge it away from Herro (MIA) as he receives the pass.
Lowry (MIA) makes clean ball contact to deflect it away from Achiuwa (TOR), and any ensuing follow-through contact after the ball is dislodged is incidental.
Lowry (MIA) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Toronto.
Vincent (MIA) and Siakam (TOR) briefly engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs off-ball before the pass.
Vincent (MIA) cleanly dislodges the ball from Siakam (TOR), and any ensuing arm contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
Siakam (TOR) rests his slightly extended forearm to Vincent's (MIA) body and marginal contact occurs as he releases away at the end of the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) is in the paint for less than three seconds prior to the Siakam (TOR) losing control of the ball.
Anunoby (TOR) is retreating his arm into a vertical position and absorbs the marginal contact from Butler (MIA) during his driving shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) establishes himself in Lowry's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Siakam (TOR) and Lowry (MIA) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Lowry (MIA) and Siakam (TOR) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs prior to receiving the entry pass.
Lowry (MIA) cleanly dislodges the ball from Siakam (TOR) on the perimeter.
Lowry (MIA) rests a hand on Siakam's (TOR) back and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Strus (MIA) legally contests Trent Jr.'s (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Anunoby (TOR) engages with Adebayo (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as he immediately slides his hand off Adebayo's arm during the screen.
Adebayo (MIA) firms up in Siakam's (TOR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Strus (MIA) reaches for the ball and makes contact with Anunoby's (TOR) face, which affects his SQBR.
VanVleet (TOR) engages with Strus (MIA) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet (TOR) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Butler (MIA) jumps slightly forward toward Anunoby (TOR) and marginal contact occurs as he makes his intended pass.
Achiuwa (TOR) gathers the pass on his left foot and takes two steps before his shot attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) swipes down and initiates contact with Achiuwa's (TOR) shoulder, which affects his play at the basket.
Anunoby (TOR) cleanly blocks the shot out of bounds. Possession is correctly maintained by Miami.
Siakam (TOR) legally contests Strus' (MIA) jump shot attempt.
